-- Refinery Patrol — merge queue processor patrol loop.
-- The Engineer in the engine room. Process polecat branches one at a time.

## refinery-patrol

  input param.wisp_type : str default("patrol")
  input param.integration_branch_refinery_enabled : str default("true")
  input param.integration_branch_auto_land : str default("false")
  input param.run_tests : str default("true")
  input param.setup_command : str default("")
  input param.typecheck_command : str default("")
  input param.lint_command : str default("")
  input param.test_command : str default("go test ./...")
  input param.build_command : str default("")
  input param.target_branch : str default("main")
  input param.delete_merged_branches : str default("true")
  input param.judgment_enabled : str default("false")
  input param.review_depth : str default("standard")

  # inbox-check : llm
    system>
      You are the Refinery checking mail for MERGE_READY submissions.
      Clean up wisps first, then process inbox.
    user>
      ```bash
      bd mol wisp gc --closed --force
      bd mol wisp gc --age 1h --force
      gt mail inbox
      ```
      For each MERGE_READY: extract branch, issue, polecat name, MR bead ID.
      Track polecat name + MR bead ID + message ID for merge-push step.
      For PATROL_WAKE: acknowledge and archive.
      For HELP: assess and escalate if needed.
      For HANDOFF: absorb context and archive.
    accept>
      Inbox processed. Merge queue populated.
  #/

  # queue-scan : llm
    - inbox-check
    system>
      You are scanning the beads merge queue. This is the source of truth.
    user>
      ```bash
      git fetch --prune origin
      gt mq list
      ```
      For each MR, verify the branch exists:
      ```bash
      git branch -r | grep <branch>
      ```
      If branch missing: `bd close <mr-id> --reason "Branch no longer exists"`
      If queue empty, skip to check-integration-branches.
    format> queue
      { mr_count: number, verified: [str], orphaned: [str] }
  #/

  # process-branch : llm
    - queue-scan
    system>
      You are performing mechanical rebase. Do NOT write application code.
      Determine rebase target using Target Resolution Rule:
      if integration_branch_refinery_enabled=true, use MR target when present,
      otherwise {{param.target_branch}}.
    user>
      Pick next branch from queue. Verify branch still exists:
      ```bash
      git ls-remote --exit-code origin refs/heads/<polecat-branch>
      ```
      If gone: close MR bead, archive mail, skip to loop-check.
      Attempt rebase:
      ```bash
      git checkout -b temp origin/<polecat-branch>
      git rebase origin/<rebase-target>
      ```
      If conflicts: abort rebase, create conflict-resolution task, skip branch.
      Never delete a branch that has conflicts.
    format> rebase
      { result: str, branch: str, conflict_task: str }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.result in ["success", "conflict", "branch_gone"];
    ```
  #/

  # run-tests : script
    - process-branch
    ```bash
    EXIT=0
    if [ -n "{{param.setup_command}}" ]; then
      {{param.setup_command}} || EXIT=1
    fi
    if [ -n "{{param.typecheck_command}}" ]; then
      {{param.typecheck_command}} || EXIT=1
    fi
    if [ -n "{{param.lint_command}}" ]; then
      {{param.lint_command}} || EXIT=1
    fi
    if [ -n "{{param.build_command}}" ]; then
      {{param.build_command}} || EXIT=1
    fi
    if [ "{{param.run_tests}}" = "true" ] && [ -n "{{param.test_command}}" ]; then
      {{param.test_command}} || EXIT=1
    fi
    if [ $EXIT -eq 0 ]; then
      echo "tests_pass"
    else
      echo "tests_fail"
    fi
    ```
  #/

  # quality-review : llm
    - run-tests
    system>
      You are reviewing the merge diff for quality issues.
      Phase 1: measurement only — reviews do NOT gate merges.
      Depth: {{param.review_depth}}.
    user>
      If "{{param.judgment_enabled}}" != "true", skip: "Quality review skipped."
      Otherwise review the diff:
      ```bash
      git diff origin/{{param.target_branch}}...temp
      ```
      Assess: correctness, security, clarity, style.
      Score 0.0-1.0. Recommend approve (>=0.45) or request_changes (<0.45).
      Record result as wisp. Do NOT block merge.
    format> review
      { score: number, recommendation: str, issues: number }
  #/

  # handle-failures : decision
    - quality-review
    system>
      You enforce the Beads Promise. If checks passed, auto-complete.
      If failed, diagnose: branch regression or pre-existing?
      Branch caused it: abort merge, reopen issue, notify witness, close MR bead,
      delete branch, archive mail, skip to loop-check.
      Pre-existing: file bead (check for duplicates first), proceed with merge.
      FORBIDDEN: writing application code.
    user>
      If all checks passed: proceed to merge.
      If any failed: diagnose and handle per the protocol.
      Rejection checklist: reopen issue, MERGE_FAILED mail, close MR, delete branch, archive.
    format> verdict
      { pass: boolean, action: str, reason: str }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.action in ["merge", "reject", "proceed_preexisting"];
    ```
  #/

  # merge-push : script
    - handle-failures
    ```bash
    # Merge and push
    git checkout {{param.target_branch}}
    git merge --ff-only temp
    git push origin {{param.target_branch}}

    # Verify push succeeded
    git fetch origin
    LOCAL_SHA=$(git rev-parse {{param.target_branch}})
    REMOTE_SHA=$(git rev-parse origin/{{param.target_branch}})
    if [ "$LOCAL_SHA" != "$REMOTE_SHA" ]; then
      echo "PUSH_FAILED"
      exit 1
    fi
    echo "merge_pushed"
    ```

    ```oracle
    assert output contains "merge_pushed";
    reject if output contains "PUSH_FAILED";
    ```
  #/

  # post-merge : llm
    - merge-push
    system>
      You are completing post-merge notifications and cleanup.
      All steps are REQUIRED before proceeding.
    user>
      Send MERGED notification:
      ```bash
      gt mail send <rig>/witness -s "MERGED <polecat>" -m "Branch: <branch>
      Issue: <issue>
      Merged-At: $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)"
      ```
      Run post-merge cleanup:
      ```bash
      gt mq post-merge <rig> <mr-bead-id>
      ```
      Archive MERGE_READY mail:
      ```bash
      gt mail archive <message-id>
      ```
      Delete temp branch:
      ```bash
      git branch -d temp
      ```
    accept>
      MERGED mail sent, MR closed, issue closed, mail archived.
  #/

  # loop-check : decision
    - post-merge
    system>
      You are checking for more branches to process.
    user>
      More branches in queue?
      If yes: return to process-branch with next branch.
      If no: continue to generate-summary.
      Track: branches_merged, branches_conflict, conflict_tasks.
    format> verdict
      { more_work: boolean, merged: number, conflicts: number }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    ```
  #/

  # generate-summary : llm
    - loop-check
    system>
      You are summarizing this patrol cycle. Be terse.
    user>
      Verify all merged branches have: MERGED mail sent, MR closed,
      issue closed, MERGE_READY archived. Do any missed now.
      Include: branches merged, test results, conflicts, tasks created.
    format> digest
      { merged: number, conflicts: number, tests_pass: boolean, summary: str }
  #/

  # check-integration-branches : llm
    - generate-summary
    system>
      You manage integration branch landing.
    user>
      If "{{param.integration_branch_refinery_enabled}}" = "false": skip.
      If "{{param.integration_branch_auto_land}}" = "false": skip.
      If both true:
      ```bash
      bd list --type=epic --status=open
      gt mq integration status <epic-id>
      ```
      If ready_to_land: `gt mq integration land <epic-id>`
      Never land partial epics.
    accept>
      Integration branches checked.
  #/

  # context-check : decision
    - check-integration-branches
    system>
      You are assessing session health for continue/handoff decision.
    user>
      Check: RSS, session age, context usage, work done this cycle.
      ```bash
      ps -o rss= -p $$
      ```
      If heavy on multiple signals, hand off. If light with active queue, continue.
    format> verdict
      { action: str, rss_mb: number, reason: str }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    assert output.action in ["CONTINUE", "HANDOFF"];
    ```
  #/

  # patrol-cleanup : llm
    - context-check
    system>
      You are cleaning up inbox at end of patrol cycle.
    user>
      ```bash
      gt mail inbox
      ```
      Archive stale messages. Check for orphaned MR beads:
      ```bash
      bd list --type=merge-request --status=open
      ```
      Verify landed work before closing any MR bead.
      Goal: inbox <=3 active messages.
    accept>
      Inbox clean.
  #/

  # burn-or-loop : script
    - patrol-cleanup
    ```bash
    if [ "{{context-check.action}}" = "HANDOFF" ]; then
      gt handoff -s "Patrol complete" -m "{{generate-summary.summary}}"
      echo "action=HANDOFF"
    else
      gt mol step await-event --channel refinery \
        --backoff-base 30s --backoff-mult 2 --backoff-max 5m --cleanup
      gt patrol report --summary "{{generate-summary.summary}}"
      echo "action=LOOP"
    fi
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: patrol include_metrics: true

##/
